{"id":208,"date":"2011-12-29T03:35:09","date_gmt":"2011-12-29T03:35:09","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/archives\/208"},"modified":"2013-02-09T13:38:35","modified_gmt":"2013-02-09T13:38:35","slug":"lorne-balfe","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/archives\/208","title":{"rendered":"Lorne Balfe&#8230;"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>If you&#8217;re a fan of <a href=\"http:\/\/www.hanszimmer.com\/\">Hans Zimmer<\/a>, here&#8217;s a tip for another composer to look out for: <a href=\"http:\/\/www.lornebalfe.com\/\">Lorne Balfe<\/a>. I was recently looking through <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hans_Zimmer_discography#2010s\">Zimmer&#8217;s discography<\/a> and noticed Balfe cropping up as co-composer or co-producer in a number of recent scores, notably recently <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sherlock_Holmes:_A_Game_of_Shadows\">Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows<\/a>. <a href=\"http:\/\/www.lornebalfe.com\/biography\/\">His brief biography<\/a> details further work with Zimmer stretching back into the previous decade including producing the original <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sherlock_Holmes_(2009_film)\">Sherlock Holmes<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Inception:_Music_from_the_Motion_Picture\">Inception<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Dark_Knight_(soundtrack)\">The Dark Knight<\/a> and providing additional music for <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pirates_of_the_Caribbean:_Dead_Man%27s_Chest_(soundtrack)\">Pirates II<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pirates_of_the_Caribbean:_At_World%27s_End_(soundtrack)\">Pirates III<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Simpsons_Movie:_The_Music\">The Simpsons Movie<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Angels_%26_Demons_(film)\">Angels &#038; Demons<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Frost\/Nixon_(film)\">Frost\/Nixon<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Personally, I like all of the soundtracks listed above &#8211; I have omitted a few from the full lists (notably, I have not heard some that I have omitted), but I find that there&#8217;s an interesting correlation between the recent soundtracks by Zimmer that I particularly enjoy and those that Lorne Balfe has been involved with. I shall definitely keep an eye out for music by Zimmer and Balfe going forward.<\/p>\n<p>I leave you with two tracks from Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows, which I enjoy.<\/p>\n<p><strong>The Red Book<\/strong><br \/>\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/j0ElKp0IwUA\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p><strong>The End?<\/strong><br \/>\n<iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"http:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/_uuV-Fu-ZZM\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>If you&#8217;re a fan of Hans Zimmer, here&#8217;s a tip for another composer to look out for: Lorne Balfe. I was recently looking through Zimmer&#8217;s discography and noticed Balfe cropping up as co-composer or co-producer in a number of recent &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/archives\/208\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[26,5],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/208"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-json\/wp\/